description: Recently sold: $45,000.

Recently sold: $300,000. This home is located in one of the most popular and newer neighborhoods in Red Wing.  It is at the upper end of Pine Ridge Blvd near Halquist Ave.  Pine Ridge Blvd slopes gently and ends in a cul-de-sac a couple blacks away.  There are also 2 neighborhood parks just before the end of the street.
This wonderful 2 story home with incredible curb appeal was built in 1993. It has 4 bedrooms, 3 on the upper level and 1 on the lower level. There are 3 bathrooms in the home.  A 3/4 bath on the main level, a walk thru full master bath on the upper level and a 3/4 bath on the lower level.  
The exterior of the home is maintenance free vinyl.  
A cement driveway leads to a 3 car garage.  The deck and patio on the back of the house measure 14 feet by 12 feet.  The deck is off of the main level and the patio is accessed via the walkout basement.  
The backyard slopes down to a wooded hillside which provides scenic views and privacy.
There is a large storage shed off the back left corner of the home that is perfect for storing tools and the lawn mower.  The front porch measures 12 feet by 4 feet.
As you enter the main level of the home, you will notice that the open floor plan gives a spacious feel to the home while at the same time feeling warm and inviting.
The living room has a wonderful walk out bay window that measures 9 feet across, not counting the sides. There is one stationary window in the middle and 4 other windows that can be opened.  Another feature in the living room is the gas fireplace that has a marble hearth and surround. 
As you enter the dining room from the living room, you walk through a large archway which is really a beautiful and unique feature of the home. 
There is a patio door in the dining room that leads out to the deck. 
 Just before you enter the kitchen, you'll see a counter top eating area.  The kitchen itself has a number of wonderful features including a new tile backsplash that really enhances the beauty of the space. There is a garden window by the sink that overlooks the wooded view in the backyard.
The appliances are high end and stainless.  Just past the kitchen and near the front door is a large closet.
All 3 bedrooms on the upper level have ceiling fans and large closets.  The master bedroom also has a large walk out bay window that is 11 feet across.   
The walk thru master bathroom has a double vanity, heated ceramic floor tiles with a separate thermostat, a whirlpool bath and matching ceramic tiles on the floor and shower surround.  It is a very roomy bathroom. 
The lower level of the home features a family room , the 4th bedroom, a 3/4 bathroom, a walkout to the patio and a laundry / utility room.
This home is beautiful inside and out and we'd love to give you a tour!

description:
Recently sold: $210,000. This 4 bedroom, 3 bath home is located within walking distance to downtown Red Wing.  This level lot features a detached 1 car garage and carport with alley access so the backyard offers privacy as well as a deck that measures 8 feet by 8 feet.

The front entrance to the home is through an expansive screen porch that runs the width of the house.  The porch measures 23 feet by 9 feet and it features new carpeting.  You'll feel like you've stepped back in time when you enter of this turn of the century gem! A Large foyer, arched doorways, beautiful wood floors and an open staircase welcome you as well as numerous updates including a completely remodeled kitchen.

The main level of this home also features a living room, dining room, laundry area, new appliances and a new tile floor in the kitchen and a family room that features a gas burning fireplace as well as a 1/2 bath.

A gorgeous open staircase leads to the upper level of the home where you will find three bedrooms and a remodeled full bath.   Two of the three bedrooms have walk-in-closets that measure 7 feet by3 feet.   All three bedrooms have ceiling fans.  This upper level also features hardwood floors throughout and some wonderful built-in natural woodwork storage cabinets and drawers in the main hallway just outside the bathroom.

The attic level of the home has been converted into a fourth bedroom that measures 23 feet by 9 feet and also features new carpeting.  There is also a storage room on this level that measures 11 feet by 9 feet

If you'd like to have a showing of this home, let us know, we'd love to give you a tour!

description:
Recently sold: $476,000. ***SOLD! Please Call Tom if you are thinking about selling***

Absolutely Stunning Southwestern style 5 bedroom, 3 Bath home perched atop a bluff overlooking miles of State Forest Land. This home was custom built for the previous owner by the renowned builder Myron Alms and the quality of construction is truly amazing. The 11' tall, log beamed ceilings of the Great Room along with the open, flowing floor plan of the gourmet kitchen, dining room, deck and gazebo make this a great home for entertaining. The floor to ceiling South facing windows in the Great Room, Dining room, Main floor office and the Master Bedroom Suite really embrace the forested valley views and bring the beauty of the outdoors in.


This home was thoughtfully designed with all of the living facilities on the main floor. The walkout lower level has 3 additional bedrooms, a light and bright family room with wood burning stove and entertainment center along with a wet bar serving the amusement room. The home is set up perfectly for empty nesters with 2 Trane furnaces, one for the upper level and one for the lower level. Use the upper furnace day to day and turn on the lower furnace when the kids come home for a visit.
 

An additional parcel of land  is included with the sale of this home (PID: 34.006.2701). This extra lot is located to the South of the Property and was purchased to protect the view and privacy. There is an additional property tax of about $78 a year for this parcel.


The home cannot be seen from the street. Turn in at my yard sign & follow the driveway straight back to the home. There is a turn out 1/2 way back which could be a good spot to place another garage or out building.


Check out the 3D Virtual Tour & Aerial Drone Video at: www.BluffHome.com to see everything this property has to offer!


Recent Updates include a Brand New Roof, Exterior Paint/Stain and Interior Paint Job.


This home will truly sell itself...  Please give me a call for your private showing.


Tom

description:
Recently sold: $167,500. This modified 2 story home is located in a very peaceful setting and offers some amazing views of Sorin's Bluff.  It was built in 1958 and has 4 bedrooms. Three bedrooms are on the main level the fourth bedroom is on the upper level.  There are two full baths, one on the main level and one on the upper level. 
As you walk around the side of the home, you'll see a wooden deck that measures 16 feet  by 10 feet.  Next to the deck is a brick patio that measures 16 feet by 12 feet.   If you look up at the house, you'll see that the upper level of the home is kept cool in the Summer months with a wall unit air conditioner.  The rest of the home uses a central air conditioner.   
The exterior of the home has vinyl siding and updated thermopane windows. 
On the opposite side of the house from the deck, an asphalt driveway leads to a 1 car, tuck under garage that has access to the basement of the home. 
As you enter the home from the front door, you'll notice that the living room has updated carpeting, new replacement thermopane windows, a new entry door, white trim and coved ceilings. The room itself measures 19 feet by  12 feet.  
Just beyond the living room is the dining room which measures 9 feet by 6 feet and it has a newer laminate floor.  
The kitchen is connected to the dining room at it measures 13 feet by 9 feet.  It features a newer refrigerator, a tin backsplash and a ceiling fan. 
The side entrance to the home is off the kitchen and it offers access to the deck.  The side entrance door has also been replaced with a high efficient thermo door.
The carpeting in the main floor hallway and all 3 bedrooms on this level was replaced at the same time as the carpet in the living room.  The windows in these bedrooms have also been updated to comply with current egrees window standards.  Two of the three bedrooms also have a ceiling fan.
The full bath on the main level features an updated vanity.
The upper level of this home was built as a Mother-In-Law apartment.  The apartment has a family room that measures 19 feet by 12 feet, an efficiency sized kitchen with a sink, and a bedroom that measures 15 feet by 9 feet.  You can see Sorin Bluff from the bedroom window.  The upper level full bath is connected to the bedroom.  The rooms on this level are heated by electric baseboard heaters that have separate thermostats as well.  The apartment also features 2 large closets in the family room and access to an attic storage area. 
The lower level of the home is currently unfinished but has a recreation room, a shop area, a laundry / utility room and access to the garage.
If you would like to schedule a showing  of this home, let us know, we'd love to give you a tour!
